@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Modern Team Task Management";
}

<section class="hero-panel">
    <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">MVC + API on one shared core</p>
        <h1 class="display-title">Coordinate projects, tasks, assignments, and conversation in one clean workspace.</h1>
        <p class="muted-copy mt-3">
            TaskHub combines ASP.NET Core MVC, Identity, EF Core, and JWT-protected APIs into a single production-minded learning project.
            It is structured to feel like a lightweight collaboration tool, not a classroom scaffold.
        </p>

        <div class="button-row mt-4">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Register">Create your account</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Login">Sign in</a>
        </div>

        <ul class="stat-list mt-4">
            <li><span>Web experience</span><strong>Server-rendered MVC views</strong></li>
            <li><span>Programmatic access</span><strong>JWT-secured JSON API</strong></li>
            <li><span>Security</span><strong>Identity + project-level authorization</strong></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="metric-card">
            <span class="metric-value">Projects</span>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Owners manage membership, archive workspaces, and keep collaboration scoped correctly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <span class="metric-value">Tasks</span>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Track title, description, due date, status, priority, assignee, creator, and discussion.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <span class="metric-value">Comments</span>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Give every task a running timeline of decisions, progress, and feedback.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <span class="metric-value">API</span>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Register, log in, issue JWTs, and manage projects and tasks over REST-style endpoints.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-grid">
    <div class="col-4">
        <article class="feature-card">
            <p class="eyebrow">Shared business logic</p>
            <h2 class="card-title">MVC and API stay aligned</h2>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Project access, owner-only membership management, task assignment checks, and comment permissions all run through the same service layer.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
    <div class="col-4">
        <article class="feature-card">
            <p class="eyebrow">Deployment-ready shape</p>
            <h2 class="card-title">Environment-friendly configuration</h2>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Connection strings and JWT settings come from configuration so the app can move cleanly into containers or Azure later.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
    <div class="col-4">
        <article class="feature-card">
            <p class="eyebrow">Education without toy code</p>
            <h2 class="card-title">Readable but realistic</h2>
            <p class="content-muted mb-0">Thin controllers, view models, DTOs, EF configurations, Identity integration, migrations, and clear authorization boundaries.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-grid">
    <div class="col-8">
        <div class="surface-card">
            <div class="section-header">
                <div>
                    <p class="eyebrow mb-1">Typical workflow</p>
                    <h2>How teams move through TaskHub</h2>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <article class="timeline-card">
                    <h3 class="card-title">1. Create a project</h3>
                    <p class="content-muted mb-0">The creator becomes owner automatically and is added to the membership table with owner role.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="timeline-card">
                    <h3 class="card-title">2. Invite members</h3>
                    <p class="content-muted mb-0">Owners add collaborators by email, keeping project visibility scoped to members only.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="timeline-card">
                    <h3 class="card-title">3. Create and assign tasks</h3>
                    <p class="content-muted mb-0">Tasks can only be assigned to active users who already belong to the project.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="timeline-card">
                    <h3 class="card-title">4. Track progress</h3>
                    <p class="content-muted mb-0">Use Todo, InProgress, Done, and Blocked with visible priority markers to keep work moving.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="timeline-card">
                    <h3 class="card-title">5. Comment on work</h3>
                    <p class="content-muted mb-0">Task-level discussion creates a chronological audit trail for decisions and updates.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="timeline-card">
                    <h3 class="card-title">6. Automate with API</h3>
                    <p class="content-muted mb-0">Issue a JWT from the auth endpoints and use the same rules over JSON as the MVC site enforces.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-4">
        <div class="surface-card">
            <p class="eyebrow mb-1">API sample</p>
            <h2>JWT login flow</h2>
            <pre class="mb-0"><code>POST /api/auth/login
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
